**CSS Modules** — Scoped CSS files

```css
/* Button.module.css */
.button {
  padding: 12px 24px;
  background: blue;
  color: white;
}

.primary {
  background: #2563eb;
}
```

```tsx
import styles from './Button.module.css';

function Button() {
  return <button className={styles.button}>Click</button>;
}
```

**Pros:**
✅ Standard CSS syntax (familiar)
✅ Automatic scoping (no conflicts)
✅ Works with Sass/SCSS
✅ No extra dependencies
✅ Good for existing CSS codebases

**Cons:**
❌ Verbose (separate file for styles)
❌ No design system built-in
❌ Manual responsive design
❌ Class name management needed

---

**Tailwind CSS** — Utility-first framework

```tsx
function Button() {
  return (
    <button className="px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition">
      Click
    </button>
  );
}
```

**Pros:**
✅ Fast development (no switching between files)
✅ Consistent design system
✅ Responsive design utilities
✅ Small production bundle (purges unused styles)
✅ No naming conflicts

**Cons:**
❌ Learning curve (memorize class names)
❌ HTML can look cluttered
❌ Harder to theme dynamically
❌ Refactoring means updating many files

---

**When to use CSS Modules:**
✅ Migrating from traditional CSS
✅ Team prefers standard CSS
✅ Complex, unique designs
✅ Need full control over CSS

**When to use Tailwind:**
✅ New projects
✅ Rapid prototyping
✅ Design system / component library
✅ Team wants consistency
✅ Mobile-first responsive design

---

**Hybrid Approach:**

```tsx
// Tailwind for layout, CSS Modules for complex components
import styles from './Card.module.css';

function Card({ children }) {
  return (
    <div className="p-6 max-w-md mx-auto">  {/* Tailwind */}
      <div className={styles.cardContent}>    {/* CSS Module */}
        {children}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**`next/image`** automatically optimizes images for performance and user experience.

**Key Features:**

1. ✅ **Automatic format conversion** (WebP, AVIF)
2. ✅ **Responsive images** (srcset for different screen sizes)
3. ✅ **Lazy loading** (loads as you scroll)
4. ✅ **Blur placeholder** (smooth loading experience)
5. ✅ **Prevents layout shift** (reserves space)
6. ✅ **On-demand optimization** (not at build time)

---

**Scenario 1: Static Image (local)**

```tsx
import Image from 'next/image';
import profilePic from './profile.jpg';  // Import local image

export default function Profile() {
  return (
    <Image
      src={profilePic}  // Auto-detects width/height
      alt="Profile picture"
      placeholder="blur"  // Automatic blur placeholder
      priority  // Load immediately (above fold)
    />
  );
}
```

