**Scenario 5: Custom Blur Placeholder**

```tsx
// Generate blur data URL (at build time or server)
import { getPlaiceholder } from 'plaiceholder';

async function getImage() {
  const { base64 } = await getPlaiceholder('/image.jpg');
  return base64;
}

// Use in component
<Image
  src="/image.jpg"
  alt="Image"
  width={800}
  height={600}
  placeholder="blur"
  blurDataURL="data:image/jpeg;base64,..."  // Custom blur
/>
```

---

**Performance Tips:**

✅ Use `priority` for above-fold images only
✅ Use `loading="lazy"` for below-fold (default)
✅ Always provide `width` and `height` (prevents layout shift)
✅ Use `fill` for responsive containers
✅ Configure `remotePatterns` for external images
✅ Use blur placeholders for smooth loading

